American TV actor Morgan Stevens has died at 70. A source close to the deceased said he hadn’t been seen or heard from for a couple of days, which prompted a neighbour to alert the authorities to do a wellness check. This led to the confirmation of his death by the police as they found his dead body in his kitchen on Wednesday, January 26, 2022. Also, the police affirmed he died of natural causes as they suspect no foul play.   Ex-BBN’s Kiddwaya: My woman must have big heart     My sister is adored more than me – DJ Cuppy     Life as a single mom, by Iyabo Ojo   - Advertisement - Morgan was best known for his work on the show “Fame”, in which he played teacher David Reardon for two seasons. He was a recurring character on “Melrose Place” and “A Year in the Life”. Morgan also made guest appearances on a variety of shows, including “Murder, She Wrote”, “One Day at a Time”, and “Murder One”, with “Walker, Texas Ranger” being his last appearance on television.